AB  - Recently demands for larger and more complicated construction projects are increasing, and tremendous efforts are made to improve the productivity of construction industry. The traditional method of conducting structural design is of sequential engineering concept like point-based design in which designers determine the initial design plan based on designer's experience and judgment and then proceed with detailed design. However, Set-based Design (SBD) of concurrent engineering concept is lean design that eliminates wasting elements and increases the potential for the improvement of productivity in overall project standpoint by sharing information and collaborating with relevant fields. In addition, S-BIM (Structural Building Information Modeling) provides an environment flexible to exchange information and collaborate with relevant field for the execution of SBD. In this study, on the basis of S-BIM, a SBD procedure is established and a case study is performed with the procedure. The case study shows the proposed SBD procedure has a high efficiency in the selection of the global optimal alternatives of structural floor systems considering the constructability, structural capacity and economical feasibility simultaneously. © 2012 American Scientific Publishers. All rights reserved.
