AB  - Burgers Ergon, a subsidiary company of Heijmans N.V., one of the largest construction companies in The Netherlands, decided to undertake a Lean Six Sigma project to improve employee safety on construction sites. The Define-Measure-Analyze-Improve-Control (DMAIC) methodology was used as a framework to execute this improvement project. The project started with a clear definition of the process, as safety involved every employee engaged in physical activities. The best process capturing this part of the organization was the incident registration administration. The first step was to capture this in the Supplier-Input-Process-Output-Client (SIPOC). The next step was to translate the purpose of the project to create ideal work and production circumstances into specific and quantifiable measures, called critical-to-quality measures (CTQs). The first step after defining the CTQs was to collect data to determine the existing behavior and to establish clarity regarding the size of the problem.
