AB  - The views of Dr Mick Lynn, Tim Franklin, and John Coleman on the implementation of lean and sustainable processes in the construction sector are discussed. Lean and Sustainability can provide superior productivity, better quality, selective cost reduction, slicker supply chains, and better margins. The most well known application of Lean is by Toyota and that is the reason for which it is referred as the Toyota Production System (TPS). Eastbourne Homes Ltd, an Arms Length Management Organization, has recently undertaken its first steps in Lean. Initial results show that waiting times for disabled adaptations have been reduced by 53% and the backlog of requests for adaptations has been cut from 120 to 46. The suppliers, clients, and other stakeholders are also more deeply involved as an integral part of the process and success.
