AB  - Lean construction is about reducing waste in a given construction project. A building construction in a lean regime is designed specifically with operations in mind, therefore, research and collaboration is an essential part of the design process. Lean construction leads to reduced costs associated with waste raw material, hence, the structure's carbon footprint, reducing wasted embedded energy as well as CO2 emissions. In order to implement a lean construction strategy, end user, architect, building contractor and key suppliers must join forces to form a design collaboration. After pinpointing exact requirements with all parties at an early stage, the opportunity for design errors occuring during the build process is minimized. This facilitates a fast, uninterrupted work-flow and also should help eliminate over/under-ordering raw materials.
